  <section id="home">
    <div class="content-block">
      <h2>Course Overview</h2>
      <p>Purpose of Web Technology<br><br>
        
1.Global Information Sharing<br>
        

Example: Wikipedia allows millions to access/update knowledge instantly.<br>

Example: News websites deliver real-time updates worldwide.<br><br>

2.Seamless Communication<br>

Example: WhatsApp/Telegram for instant messaging; Zoom for video conferencing.<br>

Example: Social media (Twitter, Facebook) connects people across borders.<br><br>

3.E-Commerce & Business Growth<br>

Example: Amazon/Flipkart enable online shopping with secure payments.<br>

Example: Shopify lets small businesses create online stores easily.<br><br>

4.Online Education (E-Learning)<br>

Example: Coursera/Udemy offer courses with interactive quizzes and certificates.<br>

Example: Google Classroom facilitates virtual classrooms for schools.<br><br>

5.Entertainment & Media Streaming<br>

Example: Netflix/Spotify stream movies/music on-demand.<br>

Example: YouTube hosts user-generated content globally.<br><br>
6.Automation & Efficiency<br>

Example: Chatbots (like Zendesk) handle customer queries 24/7.<br>

Example: Online banking automates transactions without branch visits.<br><br>

7.Remote Work & Cloud Computing<br>

Example: Google Drive/Dropbox store files accessible from any device.<br>

Example: Slack/Trello enable team collaboration remotely.<br><br>

8.Data Management & Analytics<br>

Example: Firebase/MySQL manage large-scale databases for apps.<br>

Example: Google Analytics tracks website traffic and user behavior.<br><br>

9.Digital Marketing & Outreach<br>

Example: SEO tools (Ahrefs) help businesses rank higher on Google.<br>

Example: Facebook Ads target specific demographics for campaigns.<br><br>

10.Healthcare & Telemedicine<br>

Example: Practo allows online doctor consultations.<br>

Example: Fitbit apps track health metrics in real-time.<br><br>
Benefits of Web Technology<br><br>
1.Cost Savings<br>

Example: Cloud services (AWS) reduce hardware costs for startups.<br>

Example: Email replaces postal mail, saving time and money.<br><br>

2.Accessibility<br>

Example: Screen readers (like NVDA) make websites usable for the visually impaired.<br>

Example: Mobile-responsive designs work on phones/tablets.<br><br>

3.Scalability<br>

Example: Netflix scales server capacity during peak streaming hours.<br>

Example: WordPress handles traffic spikes for blogs.<br><br>
4.Security<br>

Example: HTTPS encryption protects sensitive data (credit cards).<br>

Example: Two-factor authentication (2FA) on Gmail enhances security.<br><br>

5.Innovation<br>

Example: AI chatbots (ChatGPT) improve customer service.<br>

Example: WebGL enables 3D graphics in browsers (e.g., Google Maps).<br><br>

6.Environmental Impact<br>

Example: Digital documents reduce paper waste (e.g., e-tickets).<br>

Example: Remote work cuts down on commuting emissions.<br><br>
7.User Convenience<br>

Example: Food delivery apps (Swiggy) order meals with one click.<br>

Example: Google Maps provides real-time navigation.<br><br>


</p>
    </div>
  </section>

